The paper deals with the problem of installing multiple dependent packages and learning their dependencies and conflicts. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of combinatorial data structures and algorithms for generating queries suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses lower and upper bounds on the number of queries required, which could be of interest to the machine learning community (cs.LG).
